  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes the breaking condition around an inline object.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 This enumeration describes whether a break is permitted for an inline object. This break is affected by the <xref:System.Windows.LineBreakCondition> of the inline object before it (if any). In the table below, the values across the top represent <xref:System.Windows.LineBreakCondition> values for one inline object while the values on the left represent values of another inline object. A value of "True" or "False" is indicated depending on whether a line break is permitted between the two inline objects.  
  
||||||  
|-|-|-|-|-|  
||BreakDesired|BreakPossible|BreakRestrained|BreakAlways|  
|BreakDesired|True|True|False|True|  
|BreakPossible|True|False|False|True|  
|BreakRestrained|False|False|False|True|  
|BreakAlways|True|True|True|True|  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
